    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Unstandardized name used for pigments that are blue with a greenish overtone, usually a composite pigment made from synthetic ultramarine blue and viridian.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een ongestandaardiseerde voor blauwe pigmenten met een groenachtige boventoon, meestal samengestelde pigmenten die zijn gemaakt van synthetisch ultramarijnblauw en chroomoxydehydraatgroen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一個非標準化的顏料名稱，意指略帶綠色色澤的藍色，通常是由合成群青藍和銘綠製成的合成顏料。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
